00:11:39,431 --> 00:11:41,765
Oh. Oh, please.

249
00:11:41,832 --> 00:11:43,265
It's just...

250
00:11:43,331 --> 00:11:45,731
[ Sighs ]
it doesn't sound like dan.

251
00:11:47,932 --> 00:11:48,670
What do you mean?

252
00:11:49,243 --> 00:11:51,972
Well, i would have expected
a little more grandstanding,

253
00:11:51,973 --> 00:11:52,809
That's all.

254
00:11:54,633 --> 00:11:57,466
Well, she says
he's asking for jamie.

255
00:11:57,533 --> 00:11:59,832
Thinks i should
bring him by.

256
00:11:59,899 --> 00:12:00,984
Do you think jamie
should see him like that?

257
00:12:00,985 --> 00:12:01,590
I don't know.

258
00:12:01,591 --> 00:12:04,090
After everything
he's been through with quentin

259
00:12:04,157 --> 00:12:05,958
And now seeing
dan's gravestone,

260
00:12:06,023 --> 00:12:08,390
I promised him
he could see his grandfather.

261
00:12:08,457 --> 00:12:10,224
So, what are you
gonna do?

262
00:12:10,290 --> 00:12:11,591
[ Sighs ]

263
00:12:11,657 --> 00:12:14,424
I don't know.

264
00:12:14,491 --> 00:12:17,057
Oh, i wish
nathan were here.

265
00:12:17,123 --> 00:12:18,958
You're here.

266
00:12:19,023 --> 00:12:20,624
Hey.

267
00:12:20,691 --> 00:12:23,557
So, how was your flight?
You ready for today?

268
00:12:23,624 --> 00:12:25,624
Yeah, um...
it -- It was fine.

269
00:12:25,691 --> 00:12:28,457
Listen, there's something
i really need to talk to
you about. It's important.

270
00:12:28,524 --> 00:12:31,157
And i probably should
have talked to you about
it a while ago, but --

271
00:12:31,224 --> 00:12:33,691
Look, i don't want this to be
awkward for either of us,

272
00:12:33,757 --> 00:12:34,657
All right?

273
00:12:34,724 --> 00:12:36,324
We have to work together,

274
00:12:36,390 --> 00:12:38,824
So let's not do
the heavy emotional thing.

275
00:12:40,190 --> 00:12:41,754
I'll be okay
if you're okay. Okay?

276
00:12:42,671 --> 00:12:43,353
[ Chuckles softly ]

277
00:12:44,314 --> 00:12:46,301
Wait till you see what
we have planned for you today.

278
00:12:46,302 --> 00:12:47,835
It's gonna be great.

279
00:12:50,002 --> 00:12:51,868
Starting with this.

280
00:12:57,502 --> 00:12:58,469
[ Chuckles softly ]

281
00:13:00,102 --> 00:13:02,035
So, what do you think?

282
00:13:03,494 --> 00:13:06,928
I think
it looks amazing.

283
00:13:06,995 --> 00:13:10,260
* ...running down my face *

284
00:13:10,327 --> 00:13:11,961
So, these are
your all-Time favorites?

285
00:13:13,694 --> 00:13:15,127
Um, some of them.

286
00:13:15,194 --> 00:13:17,260
<i>Some of them
just look really cool.</i>

287
00:13:19,061 --> 00:13:20,028
Hmm.

288
00:13:21,227 --> 00:13:23,361
Okay, five albums...

289
00:13:23,427 --> 00:13:24,861
Five that you couldn't
live without

290
00:13:24,928 --> 00:13:25,991
If you were stranded
on a desert island.

291
00:13:25,992 --> 00:13:27,230
Really?

292
00:13:27,231 --> 00:13:28,631
Show me a person's
favorite records,

293
00:13:28,697 --> 00:13:30,736
And i'll tell you everything
you need to know about them.

294
00:13:30,737 --> 00:13:32,704
Okay. Fine.

295
00:13:32,771 --> 00:13:36,138
But you're gonna have to
write yours down, too.

296
00:13:36,205 --> 00:13:38,370
Okay. It's a deal.

297
00:13:48,640 --> 00:13:50,309
I caught a young girl
shoplifting the other day.

298
00:13:51,310 --> 00:13:52,195
I was pretty hard
on her.

299
00:13:52,529 --> 00:13:54,296
Did you feel threatened
by her?

300
00:13:54,362 --> 00:13:55,929
No.

301
00:13:55,995 --> 00:14:00,296
No, i actually felt myself
feeling jealous.

302
00:14:01,529 --> 00:14:02,962
Jealous?

303
00:14:03,029 --> 00:14:07,462
I realize i let the company
matter too much.

304
00:14:07,529 --> 00:14:10,828
You know, we spend all this time
building something up,

305
00:14:10,895 --> 00:14:12,596
And then
we don't enjoy it.

306
00:14:12,663 --> 00:14:14,196
We just sit there,

307
00:14:14,262 --> 00:14:16,929
Terrified that someone's
gonna take it away from us.

308
00:14:19,862 --> 00:14:24,795
And she didn't answer
to anything or anyone.

309
00:14:24,862 --> 00:14:27,929
And...
that made me jealous.

310
00:14:27,995 --> 00:14:30,229
What are you
going to do about that,

311
00:14:30,296 --> 00:14:32,129
With regards
to your company?

312
00:14:32,196 --> 00:14:33,629
Well,
it doesn't matter.

313
00:14:33,695 --> 00:14:36,262
I don't have to worry about
clothes over bros anymore.

314
00:14:36,329 --> 00:14:38,062
And why's that?

315
00:14:38,129 --> 00:14:39,995
I gave it all away.

316
00:14:41,596 --> 00:14:43,929
I signed the company over
to victoria.

317
00:14:43,995 --> 00:14:45,596
Do you regret that?

318
00:14:47,196 --> 00:14:50,329
* away *

319
00:14:53,995 --> 00:14:55,196
* away *

320
00:14:55,262 --> 00:14:57,329
So, you liking
what you're seeing so far?

321
00:14:57,396 --> 00:14:59,529
[ Chuckles ] are you kidding me?
It's great.

322
00:14:59,596 --> 00:15:01,429
I got to say,
this came out of nowhere.

323
00:15:01,496 --> 00:15:04,062
I'm really, really grateful
you called.

324
00:15:04,129 --> 00:15:06,129
No, no.
Pleasure's all mine.

325
00:15:06,196 --> 00:15:08,596
I got to tell you, i've had
my eye on you for a while.

326
00:15:08,663 --> 00:15:11,029
I watched you win those
two championships at gilmore.

327
00:15:11,095 --> 00:15:12,429
I saw you play
at maryland.

328
00:15:12,496 --> 00:15:15,629
Well, thank you, but i'm
more interested in the future.

329
00:15:15,695 --> 00:15:18,029
Good. I'm glad
to hear you say that.

330
00:15:18,095 --> 00:15:21,262
'Cause we could really use
a good, young coach like you.

331
00:15:24,695 --> 00:15:26,095
Y-You want me to coach?

332
00:15:27,929 --> 00:15:29,795
<i>No, no. I thought
you wanted me to play.</i>

333
00:15:29,862 --> 00:15:32,362
Well, nathan,
your playing days are over.

334
00:15:32,429 --> 00:15:33,995
Come on.
You must know that.

335
00:15:35,229 --> 00:15:36,728
[ Scoffs ]

336
00:15:36,795 --> 00:15:39,929
* away *

337
00:15:42,220 --> 00:15:45,455
All right, number three --???

338
00:15:45,456 --> 00:15:47,700
Oh, that is
so predictable.

339
00:15:47,701 --> 00:15:49,468
"Physical graffiti."

340
00:15:49,534 --> 00:15:51,168
Whoa! Whoa!
That's cheating.

341
00:15:51,235 --> 00:15:52,868
<i>That's like two albums,
really.</i>

342
00:15:52,935 --> 00:15:55,269
Okay, fine.

343
00:15:55,270 --> 00:15:56,936
Number two --
"Nevermind,"

344
00:15:57,003 --> 00:15:59,254
And not just because
you played on it.

345
00:15:59,255 --> 00:16:01,481
"Exile on main street,"

346
00:16:01,482 --> 00:16:03,232
And that "nevermind" thing
is a rumor.

347
00:16:03,734 --> 00:16:04,483
Supposedly.

348
00:16:04,856 --> 00:16:07,732
Okay, so that leaves number one.
What do you got?

349
00:16:07,733 --> 00:16:09,869
Oh, that's easy.

350
00:16:09,870 --> 00:16:13,071
It is the first record
i ever bought --

351
00:16:13,137 --> 00:16:16,603
Elvis costello,
"my aim is true."

352
00:16:18,137 --> 00:16:19,071
What?

353
00:16:21,071 --> 00:16:23,904
[ Both laugh ]

354
00:16:27,937 --> 00:16:30,304
Hey, why do you think,
in all this time,

355
00:16:30,371 --> 00:16:32,304
My dad has
never reached out to me?

356
00:16:33,971 --> 00:16:35,937
I'm not sure
i can answer that --

357
00:16:36,004 --> 00:16:39,438
At least not in a way
that's gonna make you happy.

358
00:16:41,137 --> 00:16:43,104
Why'd they give me up?

359
00:16:44,804 --> 00:16:47,137
Peyton, we, um...

360
00:16:48,338 --> 00:16:52,204
I-I mean, all of us
were really screwed up then.

361
00:16:52,271 --> 00:16:54,470
You know, ellie
never planned for you,

362
00:16:54,537 --> 00:16:56,004
And you got to understand

363
00:16:56,071 --> 00:16:58,171
That it just
never would have worked.

364
00:17:01,438 --> 00:17:03,870
Hey, i was wondering,
um...

365
00:17:03,937 --> 00:17:06,338
If maybe you wanted
to come by tonight.

366
00:17:06,404 --> 00:17:09,071
'Cause, hopefully,
lucas will get home early,

367
00:17:09,137 --> 00:17:11,870
And i know he would
really like to meet you.

368
00:17:11,937 --> 00:17:14,971
And i just...
[ sighs ]

369
00:17:17,171 --> 00:17:20,670
I was hoping you could tell me
all about my parents.

370
00:17:20,737 --> 00:17:23,570
I want to know
about my dad.

371
00:17:23,637 --> 00:17:26,371
Be careful
what you wish for.

372
00:17:26,438 --> 00:17:28,637
Please.

373
00:17:33,004 --> 00:17:35,171
Okay.

374
00:17:35,237 --> 00:17:36,404
Be there.

375
00:17:41,937 --> 00:17:46,603
* and only the heartaches
have given me sight *

376
00:17:46,670 --> 00:17:49,004
<i>Hey, it's nate. Leave it.
[ Beep ]</i>

377
00:17:49,071 --> 00:17:52,137
Nathan, hi, i'm really sorry
to bug you up there,

378
00:17:52,204 --> 00:17:53,804
But, uh...it's about dan.

379
00:17:53,870 --> 00:17:54,745
I need to talk to you.

380
00:17:54,746 --> 00:17:57,452
I got a phone call from
his hospice nurse this morning,

381
00:17:57,453 --> 00:17:58,687
And it's not good.

382
00:17:58,754 --> 00:18:00,020
You should call me.

383
00:18:00,086 --> 00:18:01,986
I love you. Bye.

384
00:18:02,053 --> 00:18:02,986
[ Telephone beeps ]

385
00:18:03,053 --> 00:18:06,120
What's a hospice?

386
00:18:06,186 --> 00:18:08,687
Is something wrong
with grandpa?

387
00:18:08,754 --> 00:18:10,387
You said he was okay.

388
00:18:10,453 --> 00:18:12,886
I did. I know i did.

389
00:18:12,953 --> 00:18:15,587
Um...

390
00:18:15,654 --> 00:18:18,654
It turns out
grandpa's really sick.

391
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:21,053
But he's gonna
get better, right?

392
00:18:21,120 --> 00:18:23,287
[ Sighs ]
come here.

393
00:18:25,986 --> 00:18:27,353
[ Sighs ]

394
00:18:27,420 --> 00:18:29,886
Sometimes
people get so sick

395
00:18:29,953 --> 00:18:33,153
That they can't
get better.

396
00:18:33,220 --> 00:18:35,687
Is he gonna die,
like quentin?

397
00:18:35,754 --> 00:18:37,919
[ Sighs ]

398
00:18:37,986 --> 00:18:39,654
Yeah.

399
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:42,487
Yeah, i'm afraid so,
buddy.

400
00:18:42,553 --> 00:18:45,754
I didn't get to say goodbye
to quentin.

401
00:18:45,819 --> 00:18:48,786
Do i get to say goodbye
to grandpa?

402
00:18:48,853 --> 00:18:51,886
[ Inhales,
exhales deeply ]

403
00:18:51,953 --> 00:18:53,853
Yes.

404
00:18:53,919 --> 00:18:56,620
Yes, let's do that.

405
00:18:56,687 --> 00:18:58,020
Come here.

406
00:19:00,253 --> 00:19:02,320
Look, i apologize if we got
our lines crossed here.

407
00:19:02,387 --> 00:19:03,819
I just thought
that you understood

408
00:19:03,886 --> 00:19:05,786
I was interested in you
for the coaching position.

409
00:19:05,853 --> 00:19:07,086
And i-I appreciate it.

410
00:19:07,153 --> 00:19:09,020
I'm flattered, okay?
I really am.

411
00:19:09,086 --> 00:19:11,687
But i'm not ready for that yet.
I can still play.

412
00:19:11,754 --> 00:19:14,986
Nathan, that was
no small injury you suffered.

413
00:19:15,053 --> 00:19:17,020
It was spinal-Cord,
right?

414
00:19:17,086 --> 00:19:19,886
Yeah.
Yeah, it was lower-Back.

415
00:19:19,953 --> 00:19:23,253
<i>Well, most guys wouldn't even
be thinking about coming back.</i>

416
00:19:23,320 --> 00:19:25,786
They'd just be thinking
about walking right.

417
00:19:25,853 --> 00:19:27,587
I'm not most guys.

418
00:19:27,654 --> 00:19:29,020
And i can
appreciate that.

419
00:19:29,086 --> 00:19:32,387
Look, i've been rehabbing, okay?
I'm in shape. I can play.

420
00:19:32,453 --> 00:19:34,320
You just have to
let me show you.

421
00:19:36,153 --> 00:19:39,320
I have the utmost respect
for you wanting to play again.

422
00:19:39,387 --> 00:19:41,353
You're a warrior.
You always have been.

423
00:19:43,220 --> 00:19:45,020
But i'm looking
for a coach.

424
00:19:45,086 --> 00:19:48,587
Now, i've always valued
how smart a player you were.

425
00:19:48,654 --> 00:19:51,120
And i know
that you've been coaching.

426
00:19:51,186 --> 00:19:53,453
Nathan, this is
where your future is.

427
00:19:57,420 --> 00:19:59,287
All right.

428
00:20:02,687 --> 00:20:04,687
[ Cellphone beeps ]

429
00:20:06,953 --> 00:20:08,953
I hope that
you will think about it.

430
00:20:09,020 --> 00:20:11,786
I know that you will be
a great asset here,

431
00:20:11,853 --> 00:20:13,819
Very popular,
and great for attendance.

432
00:20:15,986 --> 00:20:18,520
I know
you'd do a good job.

433
00:20:20,786 --> 00:20:24,420
* i wrote myself a letter *

434
00:20:24,487 --> 00:20:27,654
* wrapped it up in plastic *

435
00:20:27,720 --> 00:20:28,986
* put it in a hole... *

436
00:20:29,053 --> 00:20:31,053
[ Cellphone ringing ]

437
00:20:33,253 --> 00:20:34,487
Hello?

438
00:20:34,553 --> 00:20:36,986
I know you're in the middle
of it. I'm sorry.

439
00:20:37,053 --> 00:20:38,720
No, it's okay.

440
00:20:38,786 --> 00:20:41,287
Kind of a break in the action
right now.

441
00:20:41,353 --> 00:20:42,186
What's up?

442
00:20:43,687 --> 00:20:44,919
Peyton?

443
00:20:44,986 --> 00:20:48,320
Um, nothing. I just wanted
to hear your voice.

444
00:20:48,387 --> 00:20:50,720
Peyton,
what's going on?

445
00:20:50,786 --> 00:20:54,253
It's mick.

446
00:20:54,320 --> 00:20:56,353
He's my father.

447
00:20:56,420 --> 00:20:59,754
<i>Wait. He said that?
I mean, he told you?</i>

448
00:20:59,819 --> 00:21:01,186
No, no, not yet.

449
00:21:01,253 --> 00:21:03,053
Um, but that's
what tonight's about.

450
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:04,587
He's coming over
for dinner.

451
00:21:04,654 --> 00:21:06,720
But you're sure
he's your dad?

452
00:21:06,786 --> 00:21:09,720
Yeah, he slipped up,
and i just --

453
00:21:09,786 --> 00:21:11,220
I know.

454
00:21:11,287 --> 00:21:14,320
I mean, i-I honestly think i've
known since the minute we met.

455
00:21:14,387 --> 00:21:18,020
But...
he's my father, luke.

456
00:21:18,086 --> 00:21:20,487
It's gonna be okay,
peyton.

457
00:21:20,553 --> 00:21:21,819
You think so?

458
00:21:21,886 --> 00:21:24,086
[ Laughs ]
'cause i'm kind of nervous.

459
00:21:24,153 --> 00:21:25,654
You're gonna do great.

460
00:21:25,720 --> 00:21:27,654
I just wish i was there.

461
00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:29,786
Luke, they're ready
for us.

462
00:21:29,853 --> 00:21:32,186
Hey, i'm sorry,
but they need me.

463
00:21:32,253 --> 00:21:35,153
Um, i'll call you
as soon as i get out, okay?

464
00:21:35,220 --> 00:21:36,153
Okay.

465
00:21:36,220 --> 00:21:37,153
Luke?

466
00:21:37,220 --> 00:21:38,387
Yeah?

467
00:21:38,453 --> 00:21:41,587
I always feel better
when i get to talk to you.

468
00:21:41,654 --> 00:21:43,420
I love you.

469
00:21:43,487 --> 00:21:44,587
Thanks.

470
00:21:44,654 --> 00:21:46,120
[ Chuckles softly ]

471
00:21:46,186 --> 00:21:48,587
Love you too. Bye.

472
00:21:50,086 --> 00:21:52,353
[ Cellphone beeps ]

473
00:21:52,420 --> 00:21:53,986
So, there you have it,
lucas.

474
00:21:54,053 --> 00:21:56,420
You'll have signings
in all the major markets.

475
00:21:56,487 --> 00:21:58,654
We're looking at a major ad buy
in print and radio.

476
00:21:58,720 --> 00:22:01,287
And we're working
on all the regional
and national talk shows.

477
00:22:01,353 --> 00:22:02,687
That sounds great.

478
00:22:02,754 --> 00:22:05,086
All that's left to discuss
is the schedule.

479
00:22:05,153 --> 00:22:08,520
We want you to start strong,
so omaha's up first on the 24th.

480
00:22:08,587 --> 00:22:10,919
Your first book
sold very well there.

481
00:22:10,986 --> 00:22:12,587
Next --
Um, excuse me.

482
00:22:12,654 --> 00:22:16,186
I have a problem
with the chicago date.

483
00:22:16,253 --> 00:22:17,453
We --

484
00:22:17,520 --> 00:22:20,186
The schedule's pretty firm
at this point.

485
00:22:20,253 --> 00:22:22,953
Yeah, i'm -- I'm sorry,
but i can't.

486
00:22:23,020 --> 00:22:25,120
Lucas, chicago's
our second-Biggest market.

487
00:22:25,186 --> 00:22:26,986
A change is gonna cost
a lot of money.

488
00:22:27,133 --> 00:22:31,661
I understand but i need to change
okay?

489
00:22:36,553 --> 00:22:39,786
Luke, can i see you
in my office for a second?

490
00:22:39,853 --> 00:22:41,353
Lucas,
what are you doing?

491
00:22:41,420 --> 00:22:43,453
This book launch
is a really big deal.

492
00:22:43,520 --> 00:22:45,086
I know that.
I just --

493
00:22:45,153 --> 00:22:47,654
<i>You know they didn't even want
to do a book tour? They didn't.</i>

494
00:22:47,720 --> 00:22:50,453
But i made them
because i believe in you
and i fight for you.

495
00:22:50,520 --> 00:22:53,654
I appreciate it.
What could possibly
be more important than chicago?

496
00:22:53,720 --> 00:22:54,953
My wedding.

497
00:22:59,420 --> 00:23:02,687
[ Sighs ]

498
00:23:02,754 --> 00:23:05,086
It's peyton.

499
00:23:05,153 --> 00:23:06,387
We're getting married.

500
00:23:06,453 --> 00:23:07,953
[ Chuckles softly ]

501
00:23:08,020 --> 00:23:10,520
And that's why
i can't go to chicago.

502
00:23:12,919 --> 00:23:14,853
I see.

